abstract: After the F.C.C.’s move to block the deal, Moody’s Investors Service says the probability of the transaction closing as originally planned has fallen to less than 50 percent.
snippet: After the F.C.C.’s move to block the deal, Moody’s Investors Service says the probability of the transaction closing as originally planned has fallen to less than 50 percent.
lead_paragraph: After the Federal Communications Commission became the second government agency to oppose AT&T’s proposed $39 billion acquisition of T-Mobile USA, what are the odds of the original deal ever closing?

headline.main: What Next for AT&T’s T-Mobile Deal?
